<P>48. The trial judge criticized a letter from Plaintiffs' Counsel which stated that, &ldquo;Ms. Carroll continues to reside in Stillwater Retirement Residence and I do not believe her needs have changed substantially.&rdquo; No evidence was called that this information was incorrect as of the date of the letter (May 2015). In fact, the defence position at trial was that recommendations of intensive therapy were made by the treatment team was &ldquo;all of a sudden&rdquo; in July and August 2015.
